body:
### Description

I'm working on software that uses github.com/docker/cli for talking to Docker. When upgrading from v28 to v29 (v29.5.2+incompatible to be specific), a new version of github.com/moby/moby/client is pulled in whose network address parsing is less lenient which causes backwards-compatibility issues when interacting with Docker 26.1.5+dfsg1 included in Debian 13.

Reproducer:

```go
package main

import (
	"context"
	"fmt"
	"log"

	"github.com/moby/moby/client"
)

func main() {
	cli, err := client.New(client.FromEnv)
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatalf("Could not connect to Docker: %s\n", err)
	}
	defer cli.Close()

	ctx := context.Background()

	_, err = cli.NetworkCreate(ctx, "test-ipv6",
		client.NetworkCreateOptions{EnableIPv6: new(true), Driver: "bridge"})
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatalf("Could not create network: %s\n", err)
	}

	result, err := cli.NetworkList(ctx, client.NetworkListOptions{})
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatalf("Could not get list of networks: %s\n", err)
	}
	for _, network := range result.Items {
		fmt.Printf("%s\n", network.Name)
	}
}
```

`go run main.go` results in an error:

```
2026/07/01 14:58:59 Could not get list of networks: ParseAddr("fd05:d0ca:2::1/112"): unexpected character, want colon (at "/112")
exit status 1 
```

The problem seems to be that the network's gateway includes a prefix:

```
$ docker inspect test-ipv6
[
    {
        "Name": "test-ipv6",
        "Id": "e23952993d18530acdcb34ef6d3cd7c0d7be7204f472a9e8165575dba580e12b",
        "Created": "2026-07-01T14:58:59.488501777+01:00",
        "Scope": "local",
        "Driver": "bridge",
        "EnableIPv6": true,
        "IPAM": {
            "Driver": "default",
            "Options": null,
            "Config": [
                {
                    "Subnet": "172.19.1.0/24",
                    "Gateway": "172.19.1.1"
                },
                {
                    "Subnet": "fd05:d0ca:2::/112",
                    "Gateway": "fd05:d0ca:2::1/112"
                }
            ]
        },
        "Internal": false,
        "Attachable": false,
        "Ingress": false,
        "ConfigFrom": {
            "Network": ""
        },
        "ConfigOnly": false,
        "Containers": {},
        "Options": {},
        "Labels": {}
    }
]
```

After a restart of Docker, the prefix is dropped and `cli.NetworkList(ctx, client.NetworkListOptions{})` succeeds, which sounds like https://github.com/moby/moby/pull/49520. In my case, it isn't an option to restart Docker after creating a network or asking people with older Docker versions to upgrade. That means that I cannot upgrade the Docker/Moby libraries and receive security updates, which is unfortunate.

Would you consider making the address parsing more lenient? Or is there an alternative?
